
[1]spontaneous

   SPONTANEOUS, a. [L., of free will.]

   1. Voluntary; acting by its own impulse or will without the incitement
   of any thing external; acting of its own accord; as spontaneous motion.

   2. Produced without being planted, or without human labor; as a
   spontaneous growth of wood.

   Spontaneous combustion, a taking fire of itself. Thus oiled canvas,
   oiled wool, and many other combustible substances, when suffered to
   remain for some time in a confined state, suddenly take fire, or
   undergo spontaneous combustion.
